IT22208262 - P.Vithusha 
Create React Countries API App : my-app

A React app that allows users to search for and view country details using the REST Countries API.

#Features 
Search by Country Name: Search for countries.

Filter by Region or Language: Filter countries by region or language.

Country Details: View information such as name, capital, population, flag, and languages.

#Installation
Clone the Repository
Install Dependencies - npm install
Create a New React App - npx create-react-app my-app
Start the App - npm start


#API Endpoints Used
GET /all: Get a list of all countries.

GET /name/{name}: Search for a country by name.

GET /region/{region}: Filter countries by region.

GET /alpha/{code}: Get country details by code.

#Run tests with - npm test


Unit & Integration Tests - npm install --save-dev @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom @testing-library/user-event

unit test - header.test.jsx , login.test.jsx , Register.test.jsx

integration teat - app.test , My collection test

performance test - Home performanace test , header performance test

##cypress - npm install cypress --save-dev || Cypress test.jsx

Security test - Security route protection 

